{"type":"text","timestamp":1780729314609,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"id":"prt_e9bbce7ec001qSyWIOQeYsVVXh","messageID":"msg_e9bbca09a001SjfgWX4haFbpKX","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","type":"text","text":"I’ll verify only the cited source locations and treat each claim adversarially against the single-user SQLite/vector-store target and the already-planned 027 items. No edits, file creation, or command execution.","time":{"start":1780729309164,"end":1780729314607},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c44fe79a54fffd0016a23c5dd25288191a011684d7de5523a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729314641,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WLqZQYbuHZPrSlfQd3ux6G8I","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/models/idempotency.py","offset":1,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/models/idempotency.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Idempotency inbox for Idempotency-Key replay (CAURA-601).\n2: \n3: A row per (tenant_id, idempotency_key) stores the request body hash\n4: and the response to replay. The hash guards against the same key\n5: being reused with a different body (which the client treats as a\n6: conflict) — that's the contract every idempotency-key standard\n7: (IETF draft, Stripe) agrees on.\n8: \n9: A short TTL keeps the table bounded; opportunistic cleanup or a\n10: periodic job (tracked separately) prunes expired rows.\n11: \"\"\"\n12: \n13: from datetime import datetime\n14: \n15: from sqlalchemy import (\n16:     Boolean,\n17:     DateTime,\n18:     Index,\n19:     Integer,\n20:     PrimaryKeyConstraint,\n21:     Text,\n22:     text,\n23: )\n24: from sqlalchemy.dialects.postgresql import JSONB\n25: from sqlalchemy.orm import Mapped, mapped_column\n26: \n27: from common.models.base import Base\n28: \n29: \n30: class IdempotencyResponse(Base):\n31:     __tablename__ = \"idempotency_responses\"\n32:     __table_args__ = (\n33:         PrimaryKeyConstraint(\n34:             \"tenant_id\", \"idempotency_key\", name=\"pk_idempotency_responses\"\n35:         ),\n36:         # TTL cleanup job scans by expires_at.\n37:         Index(\"ix_idempotency_responses_expires_at\", \"expires_at\"),\n38:     )\n39: \n40:     tenant_id: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(Text, nullable=False)\n41:     idempotency_key: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(Text, nullable=False)\n42:     request_hash: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(Text, nullable=False)\n43:     response_body: Mapped[dict] = mapped_column(\n44:         JSONB, nullable=False, server_default=text(\"'{}'::jsonb\")\n45:     )\n46:     status_code: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(Integer, nullable=False)\n47:     created_at: Mapped[datetime] = mapped_column(\n48:         DateTime(timezone=True), nullable=False, server_default=text(\"now()\")\n49:     )\n50:     expires_at: Mapped[datetime] = mapped_column(\n51:         DateTime(timezone=True), nullable=False\n52:     )\n53:     # ``true`` while the handler is still running, flipped to ``false``\n54:     # by ``idempotency_record`` once the response body is durable.\n55:     # Closes the race where two concurrent requests with the same key\n56:     # both miss the cache and both execute the handler.\n57:     is_pending: Mapped[bool] = mapped_column(\n58:         Boolean, nullable=False, server_default=text(\"false\")\n59:     )\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Idempotency inbox for Idempotency-Key replay (CAURA-601).\n\nA row per (tenant_id, idempotency_key) stores the request body hash\nand the response to replay. The hash guards against the same key\nbeing reused with a different body (which the client treats as a\nconflict) — that's the contract every idempotency-key standard\n(IETF draft, Stripe) agrees on.\n\nA short TTL keeps the table bounded; opportunistic cleanup or a\nperiodic job (tracked separately) prunes expired rows.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nfrom sqlalchemy import (\n    Boolean,\n    DateTime,\n    Index,\n    Integer,\n    PrimaryKeyConstraint,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/models/idempotency.py","text":"\"\"\"Idempotency inbox for Idempotency-Key replay (CAURA-601).\n\nA row per (tenant_id, idempotency_key) stores the request body hash\nand the response to replay. The hash guards against the same key\nbeing reused with a different body (which the client treats as a\nconflict) — that's the contract every idempotency-key standard\n(IETF draft, Stripe) agrees on.\n\nA short TTL keeps the table bounded; opportunistic cleanup or a\nperiodic job (tracked separately) prunes expired rows.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nfrom sqlalchemy import (\n    Boolean,\n    DateTime,\n    Index,\n    Integer,\n    PrimaryKeyConstraint,\n    Text,\n    text,\n)\nfrom sqlalchemy.dialects.postgresql import JSONB\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import Mapped, mapped_column\n\nfrom common.models.base import Base\n\n\nclass IdempotencyResponse(Base):\n    __tablename__ = \"idempotency_responses\"\n    __table_args__ = (\n        PrimaryKeyConstraint(\n            \"tenant_id\", \"idempotency_key\", name=\"pk_idempotency_responses\"\n        ),\n        # TTL cleanup job scans by expires_at.\n        Index(\"ix_idempotency_responses_expires_at\", \"expires_at\"),\n    )\n\n    tenant_id: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(Text, nullable=False)\n    idempotency_key: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(Text, nullable=False)\n    request_hash: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(Text, nullable=False)\n    response_body: Mapped[dict] = mapped_column(\n        JSONB, nullable=False, server_default=text(\"'{}'::jsonb\")\n    )\n    status_code: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(Integer, nullable=False)\n    created_at: Mapped[datetime] = mapped_column(\n        DateTime(timezone=True), nullable=False, server_default=text(\"now()\")\n    )\n    expires_at: Mapped[datetime] = mapped_column(\n        DateTime(timezone=True), nullable=False\n    )\n    # ``true`` while the handler is still running, flipped to ``false``\n    # by ``idempotency_record`` once the response body is durable.\n    # Closes the race where two concurrent requests with the same key\n    # both miss the cache and both execute the handler.\n    is_pending: Mapped[bool] = mapped_column(\n        Boolean, nullable=False, server_default=text(\"false\")\n    )","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":59,"totalLines":59,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/models/idempotency.py","time":{"start":1780729314627,"end":1780729314640}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c44fe79a54fffd0016a23c5e288008191938801e45b8cb0ca"}},"id":"prt_e9bbcfd3b001re4ZmbIpEppSUj","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","messageID":"msg_e9bbca09a001SjfgWX4haFbpKX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729314645,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_o8e8AVkR8V1i9VYJEjuvnq0x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/middleware/idempotency.py","offset":130,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/middleware/idempotency.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n130: async def idempotency_for(\n131:     request: Request,\n132:     tenant_id: str,\n133:     idempotency_key: str | None,\n134:     *,\n135:     source: Literal[\"header\", \"body\"] = \"header\",\n136: ) -> IdempotencyGuard | None:\n137:     \"\"\"Look up — and atomically claim — the inbox for (tenant, key).\n138: \n139:     Returns None if the key was absent. On a cache hit with a\n140:     *different* body hash, raises 422 — reusing the same key with\n141:     different content is explicitly a client error per the IETF\n142:     idempotency-key draft.\n143: \n144:     Call this inside a route handler *after* auth enforcement, so the\n145:     tenant_id passed here is already vetted.\n146: \n147:     ``source`` selects a transport-specific prefix (``\"header\"`` →\n148:     ``header:``, ``\"body\"`` → ``body:``) prepended before the lookup\n149:     so the same string value sent via different transports never\n150:     shares a cache bucket. Validation runs against the RAW key the\n151:     caller supplied; the prefix is added only for storage.\n152: \n153:     Body hashing note: uses raw request bytes. Clients retrying a write\n154:     MUST send byte-identical bodies (same JSON serializer, same key\n155:     ordering). Non-deterministic serialization will falsely flag a\n156:     retry as a conflict. Matches Stripe and the IETF draft.\n157: \n158:     Concurrency: closes the race where two requests with the same key\n159:     arrive within milliseconds. The flow is lookup → claim → poll:\n160: \n161:     1. ``get_idempotency`` reads any existing row.\n162:     2. If a completed row matches the request hash, replay it.\n163:     3. If no row, ``claim_idempotency`` atomically inserts a pending\n164:        sentinel via INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING. The winning\n165:        caller proceeds with the handler; ``record()`` flips\n166:        ``is_pending`` to False.\n167:     4. If the claim collided (a concurrent caller raced ahead between\n168:        step 1 and step 3, or the row was pending in step 1), poll the\n169:        existing row until ``is_pending`` is False, then replay.\n170: \n171:     Storage outages degrade to \"no cache\" — a lost dedup opportunity\n172:     beats a blocked write.\n173:     \"\"\"\n174:     if not idempotency_key:\n175:         return None\n176:     if not idempotency_key.strip():\n177:         raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"Idempotency-Key must not be blank\")\n178:     if len(idempotency_key) > MAX_IDEMPOTENCY_KEY_LEN:\n179:         raise HTTPException(\n180:             status_code=400,\n181:             detail=f\"Idempotency-Key must be at most {MAX_IDEMPOTENCY_KEY_LEN} characters\",\n182:         )\n183: \n184:     namespaced_key = f\"{source}:{idempotency_key}\"\n185: \n186:     body_bytes = await request.body()\n187:     request_hash = hashlib.sha256(body_bytes).hexdigest()\n188: \n189:     sc = get_storage_client()\n190: \n191:     cached: dict | None\n192:     try:\n193:         cached = await sc.get_idempotency(tenant_id, namespaced_key)\n194:     except Exception:\n195:         logger.warning(\"Idempotency lookup failed (degrading to no-cache)\", exc_info=True)\n196:         return IdempotencyGuard(tenant_id, namespaced_key, request_hash, cached=None)\n197: \n198:     if cached and not cached.get(\"is_pending\", False):\n199:         if cached[\"request_hash\"] != request_hash:\n200:             raise HTTPException(\n201:                 status_code=422,\n202:                 detail=\"Idempotency-Key reused with a different request body\",\n203:             )\n204:         return IdempotencyGuard(tenant_id, namespaced_key, request_hash, cached=cached)\n205: \n206:     if cached and cached.get(\"is_pending\", False):\n207:         # Hash-check before polling: a different body for the same key is\n208:         # always a 422 regardless of the in-flight handler's outcome,\n209:         # and the pending row already carries the original hash. Without\n210:         # this short-circuit the loser burns the full poll budget before\n211:         # getting the same 422.\n212:         if cached[\"request_hash\"] != request_hash:\n213:             raise HTTPException(\n214:                 status_code=422,\n215:                 detail=\"Idempotency-Key reused with a different request body\",\n216:             )\n217:         completed = await _poll_until_complete(sc, tenant_id, namespaced_key)\n218:         if completed is None:\n219:             raise HTTPException(\n220:                 status_code=409,\n221:                 detail=\"Idempotency-Key still in progress; retry shortly\",\n222:             )\n223:         if completed == _POLL_STORAGE_ERROR:\n224:             raise HTTPException(\n225:                 status_code=503,\n226:                 detail=\"Upstream storage unavailable; retry later\",\n227:             )\n228:         if completed == _POLL_VANISHED:\n229:             raise HTTPException(\n\n(Showing lines 130-229 of 333. Use offset=230 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"async def idempotency_for(\n    request: Request,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    idempotency_key: str | None,\n    *,\n    source: Literal[\"header\", \"body\"] = \"header\",\n) -> IdempotencyGuard | None:\n    \"\"\"Look up — and atomically claim — the inbox for (tenant, key).\n\n    Returns None if the key was absent. On a cache hit with a\n    *different* body hash, raises 422 — reusing the same key with\n    different content is explicitly a client error per the IETF\n    idempotency-key draft.\n\n    Call this inside a route handler *after* auth enforcement, so the\n    tenant_id passed here is already vetted.\n\n    ``source`` selects a transport-specific prefix (``\"header\"`` →\n    ``header:``, ``\"body\"`` → ``body:``) prepended before the lookup\n    so the same string value sent via different transports never","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/middleware/idempotency.py","text":"async def idempotency_for(\n    request: Request,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    idempotency_key: str | None,\n    *,\n    source: Literal[\"header\", \"body\"] = \"header\",\n) -> IdempotencyGuard | None:\n    \"\"\"Look up — and atomically claim — the inbox for (tenant, key).\n\n    Returns None if the key was absent. On a cache hit with a\n    *different* body hash, raises 422 — reusing the same key with\n    different content is explicitly a client error per the IETF\n    idempotency-key draft.\n\n    Call this inside a route handler *after* auth enforcement, so the\n    tenant_id passed here is already vetted.\n\n    ``source`` selects a transport-specific prefix (``\"header\"`` →\n    ``header:``, ``\"body\"`` → ``body:``) prepended before the lookup\n    so the same string value sent via different transports never\n    shares a cache bucket. Validation runs against the RAW key the\n    caller supplied; the prefix is added only for storage.\n\n    Body hashing note: uses raw request bytes. Clients retrying a write\n    MUST send byte-identical bodies (same JSON serializer, same key\n    ordering). Non-deterministic serialization will falsely flag a\n    retry as a conflict. Matches Stripe and the IETF draft.\n\n    Concurrency: closes the race where two requests with the same key\n    arrive within milliseconds. The flow is lookup → claim → poll:\n\n    1. ``get_idempotency`` reads any existing row.\n    2. If a completed row matches the request hash, replay it.\n    3. If no row, ``claim_idempotency`` atomically inserts a pending\n       sentinel via INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING. The winning\n       caller proceeds with the handler; ``record()`` flips\n       ``is_pending`` to False.\n    4. If the claim collided (a concurrent caller raced ahead between\n       step 1 and step 3, or the row was pending in step 1), poll the\n       existing row until ``is_pending`` is False, then replay.\n\n    Storage outages degrade to \"no cache\" — a lost dedup opportunity\n    beats a blocked write.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not idempotency_key:\n        return None\n    if not idempotency_key.strip():\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"Idempotency-Key must not be blank\")\n    if len(idempotency_key) > MAX_IDEMPOTENCY_KEY_LEN:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=400,\n            detail=f\"Idempotency-Key must be at most {MAX_IDEMPOTENCY_KEY_LEN} characters\",\n        )\n\n    namespaced_key = f\"{source}:{idempotency_key}\"\n\n    body_bytes = await request.body()\n    request_hash = hashlib.sha256(body_bytes).hexdigest()\n\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n\n    cached: dict | None\n    try:\n        cached = await sc.get_idempotency(tenant_id, namespaced_key)\n    except Exception:\n        logger.warning(\"Idempotency lookup failed (degrading to no-cache)\", exc_info=True)\n        return IdempotencyGuard(tenant_id, namespaced_key, request_hash, cached=None)\n\n    if cached and not cached.get(\"is_pending\", False):\n        if cached[\"request_hash\"] != request_hash:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=422,\n                detail=\"Idempotency-Key reused with a different request body\",\n            )\n        return IdempotencyGuard(tenant_id, namespaced_key, request_hash, cached=cached)\n\n    if cached and cached.get(\"is_pending\", False):\n        # Hash-check before polling: a different body for the same key is\n        # always a 422 regardless of the in-flight handler's outcome,\n        # and the pending row already carries the original hash. Without\n        # this short-circuit the loser burns the full poll budget before\n        # getting the same 422.\n        if cached[\"request_hash\"] != request_hash:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=422,\n                detail=\"Idempotency-Key reused with a different request body\",\n            )\n        completed = await _poll_until_complete(sc, tenant_id, namespaced_key)\n        if completed is None:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=409,\n                detail=\"Idempotency-Key still in progress; retry shortly\",\n            )\n        if completed == _POLL_STORAGE_ERROR:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=503,\n                detail=\"Upstream storage unavailable; retry later\",\n            )\n        if completed == _POLL_VANISHED:\n            raise HTTPException(","lineStart":130,"lineEnd":229,"totalLines":333,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/middleware/idempotency.py","time":{"start":1780729314633,"end":1780729314644}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c44fe79a54fffd0016a23c5e2881481918f3e55f13711d8df"}},"id":"prt_e9bbcfd44001ZZMOUvzrpGA1Zo","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","messageID":"msg_e9bbca09a001SjfgWX4haFbpKX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729314674,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_YKFPKDwmLL3bbeaHlNn7rbj1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/merge_enrichment_fields.py","offset":1,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/merge_enrichment_fields.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"MergeEnrichmentFields — apply LLM-inferred type/weight/title/tags/dates to memory fields.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: from datetime import datetime\n6: \n7: from core_api.constants import DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE, DEFAULT_MEMORY_WEIGHT\n8: from core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\n9: from core_api.pipeline.step import StepResult\n10: \n11: \n12: class MergeEnrichmentFields:\n13:     @property\n14:     def name(self) -> str:\n15:         return \"merge_enrichment_fields\"\n16: \n17:     async def execute(self, ctx: PipelineContext) -> StepResult | None:\n18:         data = ctx.data[\"input\"]\n19:         enrichment = ctx.data.get(\"enrichment\")\n20: \n21:         memory_type = data.memory_type\n22:         weight = data.weight\n23:         title = None\n24:         metadata = data.metadata or {}\n25:         ts_valid_start = data.ts_valid_start\n26:         ts_valid_end = data.ts_valid_end\n27: \n28:         if enrichment:\n29:             # LLM fills gaps; agent-provided values always win\n30:             if memory_type is None:\n31:                 memory_type = enrichment.memory_type\n32:             if weight is None:\n33:                 weight = enrichment.weight\n34:             title = enrichment.title or None\n35:             if enrichment.summary:\n36:                 metadata[\"summary\"] = enrichment.summary\n37:             if enrichment.tags:\n38:                 metadata[\"tags\"] = enrichment.tags\n39:             if enrichment.llm_ms:\n40:                 metadata[\"llm_ms\"] = enrichment.llm_ms\n41:             # Temporal resolution: LLM-extracted dates fill gaps\n42:             if ts_valid_start is None and enrichment.ts_valid_start:\n43:                 ts_valid_start = datetime.fromisoformat(enrichment.ts_valid_start.replace(\"Z\", \"+00:00\"))\n44:             if ts_valid_end is None and enrichment.ts_valid_end:\n45:                 ts_valid_end = datetime.fromisoformat(enrichment.ts_valid_end.replace(\"Z\", \"+00:00\"))\n46:             # PII detection\n47:             if enrichment.contains_pii:\n48:                 metadata[\"contains_pii\"] = True\n49:                 if enrichment.pii_types:\n50:                     metadata[\"pii_types\"] = enrichment.pii_types\n51: \n52:         # Apply defaults if still unset (LLM disabled or failed)\n53:         if memory_type is None:\n54:             memory_type = DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE\n55:         if weight is None:\n56:             weight = DEFAULT_MEMORY_WEIGHT\n57: \n58:         # Status: agent-provided wins, then LLM, then default \"active\"\n59:         status = data.status\n60:         if not status and enrichment:\n61:             status = getattr(enrichment, \"status\", None)\n62:         if not status:\n63:             status = \"active\"\n64: \n65:         # Write-mode metadata: track resolved mode and enrichment deferral\n66:         resolved_write_mode = ctx.data.get(\"resolved_write_mode\")\n67:         if resolved_write_mode:\n68:             metadata[\"write_mode\"] = resolved_write_mode\n69:         if resolved_write_mode == \"fast\" and enrichment is None:\n70:             metadata[\"enrichment_pending\"] = True\n71: \n72:         ctx.data[\"memory_fields\"] = {\n73:             \"memory_type\": memory_type,\n74:             \"weight\": weight,\n75:             \"title\": title,\n76:             \"metadata\": metadata,\n77:             \"ts_valid_start\": ts_valid_start,\n78:             \"ts_valid_end\": ts_valid_end,\n79:             \"status\": status,\n80:         }\n81:         return None\n\n(End of file - total 81 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"MergeEnrichmentFields — apply LLM-inferred type/weight/title/tags/dates to memory fields.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nfrom core_api.constants import DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE, DEFAULT_MEMORY_WEIGHT\nfrom core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\nfrom core_api.pipeline.step import StepResult\n\n\nclass MergeEnrichmentFields:\n    @property\n    def name(self) -> str:\n        return \"merge_enrichment_fields\"\n\n    async def execute(self, ctx: PipelineContext) -> StepResult | None:\n        data = ctx.data[\"input\"]\n        enrichment = ctx.data.get(\"enrichment\")\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/merge_enrichment_fields.py","text":"\"\"\"MergeEnrichmentFields — apply LLM-inferred type/weight/title/tags/dates to memory fields.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nfrom core_api.constants import DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE, DEFAULT_MEMORY_WEIGHT\nfrom core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\nfrom core_api.pipeline.step import StepResult\n\n\nclass MergeEnrichmentFields:\n    @property\n    def name(self) -> str:\n        return \"merge_enrichment_fields\"\n\n    async def execute(self, ctx: PipelineContext) -> StepResult | None:\n        data = ctx.data[\"input\"]\n        enrichment = ctx.data.get(\"enrichment\")\n\n        memory_type = data.memory_type\n        weight = data.weight\n        title = None\n        metadata = data.metadata or {}\n        ts_valid_start = data.ts_valid_start\n        ts_valid_end = data.ts_valid_end\n\n        if enrichment:\n            # LLM fills gaps; agent-provided values always win\n            if memory_type is None:\n                memory_type = enrichment.memory_type\n            if weight is None:\n                weight = enrichment.weight\n            title = enrichment.title or None\n            if enrichment.summary:\n                metadata[\"summary\"] = enrichment.summary\n            if enrichment.tags:\n                metadata[\"tags\"] = enrichment.tags\n            if enrichment.llm_ms:\n                metadata[\"llm_ms\"] = enrichment.llm_ms\n            # Temporal resolution: LLM-extracted dates fill gaps\n            if ts_valid_start is None and enrichment.ts_valid_start:\n                ts_valid_start = datetime.fromisoformat(enrichment.ts_valid_start.replace(\"Z\", \"+00:00\"))\n            if ts_valid_end is None and enrichment.ts_valid_end:\n                ts_valid_end = datetime.fromisoformat(enrichment.ts_valid_end.replace(\"Z\", \"+00:00\"))\n            # PII detection\n            if enrichment.contains_pii:\n                metadata[\"contains_pii\"] = True\n                if enrichment.pii_types:\n                    metadata[\"pii_types\"] = enrichment.pii_types\n\n        # Apply defaults if still unset (LLM disabled or failed)\n        if memory_type is None:\n            memory_type = DEFAULT_MEMORY_TYPE\n        if weight is None:\n            weight = DEFAULT_MEMORY_WEIGHT\n\n        # Status: agent-provided wins, then LLM, then default \"active\"\n        status = data.status\n        if not status and enrichment:\n            status = getattr(enrichment, \"status\", None)\n        if not status:\n            status = \"active\"\n\n        # Write-mode metadata: track resolved mode and enrichment deferral\n        resolved_write_mode = ctx.data.get(\"resolved_write_mode\")\n        if resolved_write_mode:\n            metadata[\"write_mode\"] = resolved_write_mode\n        if resolved_write_mode == \"fast\" and enrichment is None:\n            metadata[\"enrichment_pending\"] = True\n\n        ctx.data[\"memory_fields\"] = {\n            \"memory_type\": memory_type,\n            \"weight\": weight,\n            \"title\": title,\n            \"metadata\": metadata,\n            \"ts_valid_start\": ts_valid_start,\n            \"ts_valid_end\": ts_valid_end,\n            \"status\": status,\n        }\n        return None","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":81,"totalLines":81,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/pipeline/steps/write/merge_enrichment_fields.py","time":{"start":1780729314667,"end":1780729314673}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c44fe79a54fffd0016a23c5e288208191b41322a3e66f0967"}},"id":"prt_e9bbcfd4a001Kib7YZImcQuIC3","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","messageID":"msg_e9bbca09a001SjfgWX4haFbpKX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729314682,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_p7SuXx71g0PUKZVhNDiHbMEq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","offset":1640,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1640:     agent_id: str,\n1641:     tenant_config: object,\n1642:     *,\n1643:     agent_provided_fields: list[str] | None = None,\n1644:     reference_datetime: datetime | None = None,\n1645: ) -> None:\n1646:     \"\"\"Enrichment counterpart of :func:`_schedule_embed_or_reembed`.\n1647: \n1648:     Inline mode (OSS / pre-CAURA-595 default): run enrichment as an\n1649:     in-process background task in core-api via\n1650:     :func:`_enrich_memory_background`.\n1651:     Deferred mode (CAURA-595 SaaS): publish ``ENRICH_REQUESTED``;\n1652:     ``core-worker`` consumes the event, runs the LLM, and PATCHes the\n1653:     enrichment fields back. The worker also emits ``ENRICHED`` after\n1654:     the PATCH lands.\n1655: \n1656:     ``agent_provided_fields`` is forwarded so the worker doesn't\n1657:     overwrite anything the agent set explicitly at write time —\n1658:     critical because ``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n1659:     ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)`` and would otherwise downgrade\n1660:     those columns on every redelivery.\n1661:     \"\"\"\n1662:     if settings.inline_enrichment:\n1663:         # NOTE: ``agent_provided_fields`` and ``reference_datetime``\n1664:         # are intentionally NOT forwarded to ``_enrich_memory_background``.\n1665:         # The inline path pre-dates these concepts and uses an\n1666:         # equivalent gate by reading the row's current value vs the\n1667:         # schema default (``if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and\n1668:         # enrichment.memory_type:`` etc., see the body of\n1669:         # ``_enrich_memory_background``). When the agent set\n1670:         # ``memory_type=\"rule\"`` the column already reads ``\"rule\"``\n1671:         # not ``\"fact\"``, and the inline gate skips.\n1672:         #\n1673:         # The two paths converge on the same agent-wins outcome via\n1674:         # different mechanisms; unifying them on\n1675:         # ``agent_provided_fields`` is a reasonable cleanup but out of\n1676:         # scope for CAURA-595 — there's no observable behavioural\n1677:         # delta between the gates today.\n1678:         await _enrich_memory_background(memory_id, content, tenant_id, fleet_id, agent_id)\n1679:     else:\n\n(Showing lines 1640-1679 of 3230. Use offset=1680 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    agent_id: str,\n    tenant_config: object,\n    *,\n    agent_provided_fields: list[str] | None = None,\n    reference_datetime: datetime | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Enrichment counterpart of :func:`_schedule_embed_or_reembed`.\n\n    Inline mode (OSS / pre-CAURA-595 default): run enrichment as an\n    in-process background task in core-api via\n    :func:`_enrich_memory_background`.\n    Deferred mode (CAURA-595 SaaS): publish ``ENRICH_REQUESTED``;\n    ``core-worker`` consumes the event, runs the LLM, and PATCHes the\n    enrichment fields back. The worker also emits ``ENRICHED`` after\n    the PATCH lands.\n\n    ``agent_provided_fields`` is forwarded so the worker doesn't\n    overwrite anything the agent set explicitly at write time —\n    critical because ``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n    ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)`` and would otherwise downgrade","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","text":"    agent_id: str,\n    tenant_config: object,\n    *,\n    agent_provided_fields: list[str] | None = None,\n    reference_datetime: datetime | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Enrichment counterpart of :func:`_schedule_embed_or_reembed`.\n\n    Inline mode (OSS / pre-CAURA-595 default): run enrichment as an\n    in-process background task in core-api via\n    :func:`_enrich_memory_background`.\n    Deferred mode (CAURA-595 SaaS): publish ``ENRICH_REQUESTED``;\n    ``core-worker`` consumes the event, runs the LLM, and PATCHes the\n    enrichment fields back. The worker also emits ``ENRICHED`` after\n    the PATCH lands.\n\n    ``agent_provided_fields`` is forwarded so the worker doesn't\n    overwrite anything the agent set explicitly at write time —\n    critical because ``EnrichmentResult``'s Pydantic defaults survive\n    ``model_dump(exclude_none=True)`` and would otherwise downgrade\n    those columns on every redelivery.\n    \"\"\"\n    if settings.inline_enrichment:\n        # NOTE: ``agent_provided_fields`` and ``reference_datetime``\n        # are intentionally NOT forwarded to ``_enrich_memory_background``.\n        # The inline path pre-dates these concepts and uses an\n        # equivalent gate by reading the row's current value vs the\n        # schema default (``if mem.get(\"memory_type\") == \"fact\" and\n        # enrichment.memory_type:`` etc., see the body of\n        # ``_enrich_memory_background``). When the agent set\n        # ``memory_type=\"rule\"`` the column already reads ``\"rule\"``\n        # not ``\"fact\"``, and the inline gate skips.\n        #\n        # The two paths converge on the same agent-wins outcome via\n        # different mechanisms; unifying them on\n        # ``agent_provided_fields`` is a reasonable cleanup but out of\n        # scope for CAURA-595 — there's no observable behavioural\n        # delta between the gates today.\n        await _enrich_memory_background(memory_id, content, tenant_id, fleet_id, agent_id)\n    else:","lineStart":1640,"lineEnd":1679,"totalLines":3230,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","time":{"start":1780729314672,"end":1780729314681}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c44fe79a54fffd0016a23c5e288288191bef0b99d5df7e875"}},"id":"prt_e9bbcfd6d001xalzDvyHx4bSp5","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","messageID":"msg_e9bbca09a001SjfgWX4haFbpKX"}}
