{"type":"text","timestamp":1780729336199,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"id":"prt_e9bbd3328001y8BFYrrAd9k6Hx","messageID":"msg_e9bbd27c7001svXyOVtnZRLG5m","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","type":"text","text":"C3’s citation is split: the advisory `near_duplicate_of` evidence exists in `detect_near_duplicate.py`, but `check_semantic_duplicate.py` is a hard-reject gate, so the combined claim overstates “preview, not hard reject.” For C4, the cited embedding service currently shows retry/degraded behavior, not model tuple or chunk fingerprinting; I’m checking the model and storage files for the exact persistence evidence.","time":{"start":1780729328424,"end":1780729336198},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08203ad48ec1a051016a23c5f06dac81918a8e64ed87d0bb37","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780729336242,"sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4zdsYMCmDq4hf4UYspfyq1RW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/embedding/_service.py","offset":241,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/embedding/_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n241:     returns ``None`` rather than raising, so write paths can persist\n242:     rows with ``embedding=NULL`` and let the async-embed worker backfill.\n243:     The same ``None`` is returned on a registry-level\n244:     ``ValueError`` (env-var misconfiguration) — see\n245:     :func:`_resolve_provider_or_degrade`.\n246: \n247:     This is the document/ingest path. For search-side queries that should\n248:     pass through an instruction-aware encoder (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct,\n249:     etc.), use :func:`get_query_embedding` instead.\n250:     \"\"\"\n251:     provider = await _resolve_provider_or_degrade(tenant_config, \"Embedding\")\n252:     if provider is None:\n253:         return None\n254:     return await _run_with_retry(lambda: provider.embed(text), \"Embedding\")\n255: \n256: \n257: async def get_query_embedding(\n258:     text: str,\n259:     tenant_config: object | None = None,\n260:     instruction: str | None = None,\n261: ) -> list[float] | None:\n262:     \"\"\"Generate a query-side embedding (instruction-aware, asymmetric).\n263: \n264:     For instruction-aware models (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct, KaLM), the\n265:     query encoder expects a task-description prefix that documents do not\n266:     receive. Symmetric providers (OpenAI ``text-embedding-3-small``,\n267:     ``bge-m3``, ``gte-en-v1.5``, ``Fake``, ``Local``, ``Vertex``) do not\n268:     implement :class:`~common.embedding.protocols.InstructionAwareEmbedder`\n269:     — the call site below detects that and falls back to the symmetric\n270:     :meth:`embed` path, matching :func:`get_embedding`.\n271: \n272:     Same retry / degradation semantics as :func:`get_embedding`: returns\n273:     ``None`` after exhausted retries rather than raising, so search routes\n274:     can degrade gracefully (typically by raising 503 to the caller). The\n275:     same ``None`` is returned on a registry-level ``ValueError`` (env-var\n276:     misconfiguration).\n277:     \"\"\"\n278:     provider = await _resolve_provider_or_degrade(tenant_config, \"Query embedding\")\n279:     if provider is None:\n280:         return None\n281: \n282:     # ``InstructionAwareEmbedder`` is an optional ``@runtime_checkable``\n283:     # Protocol declared in ``common.embedding.protocols`` for exactly\n284:     # this dispatch. Only providers backed by an instruction-aware\n285:     # model (e.g. ``OpenAIEmbeddingProvider`` pointed at\n286:     # Qwen3-Embedding) conform. ``Fake`` / ``Local`` / ``Vertex`` do\n287:     # not implement ``embed_query`` and the isinstance check returns\n288:     # False — they fall through to :meth:`embed` and silently ignore\n289:     # *instruction*.\n290:     is_instruction_aware = isinstance(provider, InstructionAwareEmbedder)\n291: \n292:     async def _call() -> list[float]:\n293:         # Inner ``def`` rather than a ``lambda`` so the closure captures\n294:         # *provider* / *text* / *instruction* with explicit ``await``\n295:         # ergonomics; ruff E731 disapproves of ``make_call = lambda:``.\n296:         if is_instruction_aware:\n297:             return await provider.embed_query(text, instruction)\n298:         return await provider.embed(text)\n299: \n300:     return await _run_with_retry(_call, \"Query embedding\")\n\n(End of file - total 300 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    returns ``None`` rather than raising, so write paths can persist\n    rows with ``embedding=NULL`` and let the async-embed worker backfill.\n    The same ``None`` is returned on a registry-level\n    ``ValueError`` (env-var misconfiguration) — see\n    :func:`_resolve_provider_or_degrade`.\n\n    This is the document/ingest path. For search-side queries that should\n    pass through an instruction-aware encoder (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct,\n    etc.), use :func:`get_query_embedding` instead.\n    \"\"\"\n    provider = await _resolve_provider_or_degrade(tenant_config, \"Embedding\")\n    if provider is None:\n        return None\n    return await _run_with_retry(lambda: provider.embed(text), \"Embedding\")\n\n\nasync def get_query_embedding(\n    text: str,\n    tenant_config: object | None = None,\n    instruction: str | None = None,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/embedding/_service.py","text":"    returns ``None`` rather than raising, so write paths can persist\n    rows with ``embedding=NULL`` and let the async-embed worker backfill.\n    The same ``None`` is returned on a registry-level\n    ``ValueError`` (env-var misconfiguration) — see\n    :func:`_resolve_provider_or_degrade`.\n\n    This is the document/ingest path. For search-side queries that should\n    pass through an instruction-aware encoder (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct,\n    etc.), use :func:`get_query_embedding` instead.\n    \"\"\"\n    provider = await _resolve_provider_or_degrade(tenant_config, \"Embedding\")\n    if provider is None:\n        return None\n    return await _run_with_retry(lambda: provider.embed(text), \"Embedding\")\n\n\nasync def get_query_embedding(\n    text: str,\n    tenant_config: object | None = None,\n    instruction: str | None = None,\n) -> list[float] | None:\n    \"\"\"Generate a query-side embedding (instruction-aware, asymmetric).\n\n    For instruction-aware models (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct, KaLM), the\n    query encoder expects a task-description prefix that documents do not\n    receive. Symmetric providers (OpenAI ``text-embedding-3-small``,\n    ``bge-m3``, ``gte-en-v1.5``, ``Fake``, ``Local``, ``Vertex``) do not\n    implement :class:`~common.embedding.protocols.InstructionAwareEmbedder`\n    — the call site below detects that and falls back to the symmetric\n    :meth:`embed` path, matching :func:`get_embedding`.\n\n    Same retry / degradation semantics as :func:`get_embedding`: returns\n    ``None`` after exhausted retries rather than raising, so search routes\n    can degrade gracefully (typically by raising 503 to the caller). The\n    same ``None`` is returned on a registry-level ``ValueError`` (env-var\n    misconfiguration).\n    \"\"\"\n    provider = await _resolve_provider_or_degrade(tenant_config, \"Query embedding\")\n    if provider is None:\n        return None\n\n    # ``InstructionAwareEmbedder`` is an optional ``@runtime_checkable``\n    # Protocol declared in ``common.embedding.protocols`` for exactly\n    # this dispatch. Only providers backed by an instruction-aware\n    # model (e.g. ``OpenAIEmbeddingProvider`` pointed at\n    # Qwen3-Embedding) conform. ``Fake`` / ``Local`` / ``Vertex`` do\n    # not implement ``embed_query`` and the isinstance check returns\n    # False — they fall through to :meth:`embed` and silently ignore\n    # *instruction*.\n    is_instruction_aware = isinstance(provider, InstructionAwareEmbedder)\n\n    async def _call() -> list[float]:\n        # Inner ``def`` rather than a ``lambda`` so the closure captures\n        # *provider* / *text* / *instruction* with explicit ``await``\n        # ergonomics; ruff E731 disapproves of ``make_call = lambda:``.\n        if is_instruction_aware:\n            return await provider.embed_query(text, instruction)\n        return await provider.embed(text)\n\n    return await _run_with_retry(_call, \"Query embedding\")","lineStart":241,"lineEnd":300,"totalLines":300,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/common/embedding/_service.py","time":{"start":1780729336237,"end":1780729336240}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08203ad48ec1a051016a23c5f82cb4819191c8767d9e23389e"}},"id":"prt_e9bbd51890019T978xjFEW63ET","sessionID":"ses_164436571ffe8MyT3INeMfMzFK","messageID":"msg_e9bbd27c7001svXyOVtnZRLG5m"}}
